Credit Card Fraud Detection – Insights
Dataset Insights
The dataset is highly imbalanced, with genuine transactions greatly outnumbering fraudulent transactions.
Fraud cases represent only a very small percentage of all transactions.
Most transactions are legitimate, making fraud detection a challenging classification problem.
Model Insights
Random Forest effectively identifies patterns associated with fraudulent activities.
Precision and Recall are more important than Accuracy because of class imbalance.
A high Recall helps minimize missed fraud cases.
Feature importance analysis identifies the most influential transaction attributes.
Business Insights
Early fraud detection can reduce financial losses.
Automated fraud detection systems improve transaction security.
Financial institutions can use the model to flag suspicious transactions for further investigation.
